         <abstract id="aspace_e1402578b5db340549be76db414a236d">The papers consist of correspondence and other papers relating to nineteenth century socialism in England and the United States. Included are two literary manuscripts by William Riley entitled Literary Cranks by One of Them and Radical Jack; copies of periodicals edited by Riley; and letters from Walter Besant, Edward Everett Hale, Rudyard Kipling, Justin McCarthy, Karl Marx, William Rossetti and John Ruskin.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname source="local">
               <part>Riley, William Harrison, 1835-1907</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
